< review>
Outrageous fees and insensitive owners.
After returning from Thanksgiving in Texas (95 year old mother-in-law and 98 year old father-in-law), my RV was towed while I was out of town.
Yes, got caught in the 72 hour "move-it" ordinance.
Luckily the Lompoc Police Dept. waived the $175 fine (thanks Sgt. Magana!), but this company is demanding $1200 as of Dec. 2, 2019 and adding $125/day!! No compromise.
Even after the PD waived the fine!!!
I offered to pay $300-$400 this morning, but Kimberly said no, that "We're in the business of towing, and no negotiation". Unbelievable.
They should be ashamed of their unwillingness to work with me on this.
I will not let this go, and will see them in Court.</review>

In the city to visit a customer and in the mood for Asian food. We decided for this place, looks like a little hole in the wall but is bigger inside than it looks. <rating>5<//rating>< Review>
Love Lady Bug's! They actually catered my wedding a few years ago. Great Japanese-Hawaiian plate lunch food. Their chicken katsu plate lunch is my favorite. For around $7.50 (in 2016, at least), you can get a hearty plate of chicken katsu, white rice, green salad, and mac salad. They also have great kalbi, chicken teriyaki, sushi, and other yummy dishes.

This is a must if you're ever craving good Japanese American/Hawaiian food!<//Review>

<user_id>111862817126800695318<//user_id>< username>
Lake Nipissing<//username>
<Date>1519284646092< /Date>< rating>
5</rating>
<Text>This was one of my favorite restaurants ever - and now it is SHUT. The location was simply incredible, with a very laid-back atmosphere. Food was always excellent, and service friendly. Today, February 20, 2018, one of the last mom and pop 'surf shack' cafes was LOST FOREVER due to lease renewal greed for the location by the City of Seal Beach. An iconic place is now gone. The City of Seal Beach has no idea how upset they have made both regular locals and visitors from outside of the country like me by outing this place. Apparently many regulars were in tears to learn of River's End being shut.
Until I was talking with the owners while they were removing all of the fittings from the restaurant today, I had no idea they were even looking after the cleaning and supplies for the public beach restrooms in the adjacent building, in addition to their own restrooms.
To all involved with River's End: thanks for a great 20 years... people really appreciated what you were doing.
Losing River's End is a HUGE LOSS for both Seal Beach and California.
Greed knows no bounds.<//Text>< pictures>

<text>Located at the end of the San Gabriel River bike route, River's End Cafe is a wonderfully informal, delicious place to treat ourselves before heading home. Although they have delicious-looking lunch choices, I have only ordered breakfast, as have my fellow riders. I can say the eggs Benedict, chilaquiles, and omelettes are great, as is the service. < Review>
Me and my brother rode form the Santa Fe Dam to Seal Beach, and one of the places I wanted to hit was the River's End Cafe. I thought it was so neat to be sitting on the patio, having lunch right on the beach!

That said, the food was ok. It's essentially bar food, so greasy and tasty. Their prices are high. Their service is very slow.

If you don't mind dropping 10 bucks for burgers and fries and aren't in a hurry, it's a nice place.< /Review>

I went to this place years ago for breakfast. Although the location is beautiful, the service was terrible (slow). Sitting on the patio, I had to go in to make sure they knew someone was out there. After ordering the eggs benedict and waiting too long again, it was terrible! The server never came back out to check so I had to go inside again to request to send it back. I next ordered the breakfast combo of eggs, bacon & toast, but when the bill came was charged for both!! Also, my husband wanted to wash his hands before eating & was told they don't have a restroom in the restaurant. He had to go to the public restroom on the beach which was filthy! Gave 1 star for location only.<//review>

< Review>
The only reason I keep coming here is the location, I like to get my exercise by bicycling along the San Gabriel river and my sister just so happens to live a mile away, so after I bike 24 miles this is a convenient spot to meet my sister for breakfast or lunch.

The service is atrocious - slow no matter how many servers or how many patrons, the food is just passable - how they can mess up making an egg or making a sandwich is beyond me.  Apathetic,  lazy, uninterested in doing their job but boy they are right on top of noticing that the bill is ready to be paid.  If they were only this good at noticing that my drink is in need of being refilled I could leave a better tip.<//Review>

<Review>A very casual Beach Shack Diner thAt sits directly on the San Gabriel River as it meets the Pacific Ocean in Seal Beach. The river divides the Cities of Long Beach & Seal Beach. The property was resurrected 5 years ago from abandonment. It was a. Boarded up building with weed growing in cracked asphalt & concrete sidewalks. Now is is a tropical Beach Patio connecting the popular bike trails with a million dollar view of the beach and ocean beyond. < user>
112506937220109403064<//user>
<Name>Gianna Grisolia< /Name>< time>
1436391713135</time>
<Rating>1<//Rating>< Text>
Do not go here!
This use to be a staple for our family, and would enjoy brunch mimosas and revel in the view with friendly service!
We came here for Father's Day, knowing full well it would be busy, placing our names on a list and waited patiently for a four person table.
We came in at ten thirty, and after an hour of viewing several tables open with no one being called to be seated, the tables just sitting open, we were getting very antsy and annoyed.
They wouldn't even let us sit at a vacant table and just order a drink!
A couple walked in at around twelve (still not seated, and no names having been called!), put there name at the bottom of the list, and once they were done, a worker from the back came forward immediately hugged the man and ushered him inside to be seated, saying 'I got you bro!'.
We immediately asked to speak to a manager, and we're told that we wouldn't be allowed to speak to a manager, he was busy.
The workers began to laugh and chat in Spanish, unaware that my entire family speaks Spanish as they bad mouthed us, thinking it was hilarious to call us names! Just because a person appears to be a different culture than you doesn't mean we don't speak the same language idiots!
This is fathers days mind you, so we were really trying not to get to upset, or upset our father who thankfully didn't hear them!
A young kid came out and announced that the kitchen was backed up and no one else would be seated for an hour, when no one had been seated for over two hours!
We'd already waited and knew we wouldn't be able to go anywhere else in time, so had to wait if we wanted to eat before my family left back home!
We were seated at 1:20pm, and were told we had to order right away cause kitchen was closing at two, and they had no bacon or sausage either. (What brunch place runs out of these breakfast staples??)

<Review>China Caff is by far one of the best and affordable Chinese food restaurants in Merced. Customer Service is amazing. The people that work there are polite and welcoming. The food portions are hearty, so you will leave with leftovers (if you choose to keep your food). Plenty of options in combo plates to choose from. The appetizers are a bit pricey for an appetizer, but they are tasty. Customers have the option to dine in or take to go. Overall, great vibes all around.

The sesame chicken tasted fine, but the flour still had a raw edge to it. The chicken chow mein is decent enough, although Im leaning more towards the egg fried rice.

The service was alright, and the prices are really the only redeeming aspect of this restaurant.</Review>

<Text>Backstory:
I went to a different chiropractor for my back pain and he put me on this long drawn out plan that cost me nearly $1k, and he didnt relieve the back pain and i also walked away with HORRIBLE neck pain - my neck started to creek and crack when i would rotate it in any direction, cause several headaches a week, and would make it nearly impossible to work (i work at a desk to top it all off).  Sleeping was also a problem.

Just finished my 6th session with Dr. Richter and my neck finally isnt causing me DAILY pain. my neck pain would get so bad that it would literally bring me to tears (and id like to think im pretty tough!). The improvement is beyond significant. i wish i would have came to here in the first place but i was won over by the high volume of reviews from the other chiropractor. Dr. Richter stays super busy and i became really encouraged during my second visit when i over hear a patient talking about how they also had horrible issues and no other chiropractor was able to fix it, yet Dr. Richter was already relieving their pain.

There has been a couple times that he will adjust me, and ill walk to my car and i'll still feel something needs popped, and he never had a problem with re-seeing me to make sure he got everything he could.

Also! the way he does Xrays was different from the other chiropractor i had went to - Dr Richter took Xrays of my neck in different positions (so he can see the motion), and then he breaks it down and shows you which areas aren't moving properly .

HIGHLY recommend coming here! His experience shows and i am so grateful to finally have relief! Thank you so much for your dedication and for being so caring by not rushing in and out & really taking time to evaluate me before every single adjustment!</Text><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< Resp>

< Text>
I woke up one morning with severe neck pain that began to travel to my left shoulder. I tried everything to calm it, ice, meds, stretching. Nothing worked. The pain was so bad that I couldn't even sit to work on the computer. I finally got in to see Dr. Richter. I was first evaluated thoroughly and shown where my problem was, but also shown that the condition was a developing problem that could potentially become a permanent, unchangeable condition. Having extensive knowledge in anatomy, plus my own history of body abuse in life, I wasn't too surprised but yes, it is a shocking reality. Since starting treatments, not only do I feel a thousand times better, but I can turn my head much more than before and without pain!! Also, my chronic low back is feeling better since I decided to get treatment for that problem too. So, not only does the unique and on-point adjustments provided each time feel tailored for what ever I'm feeling, also the rest of the services provided, such as the massage roller table, the neck decompression, and the stimulation, help me feel amazing!! This is also all provided by a very kind, caring, and welcoming staff. I'm glad I found this place.<//Text>

< review>
I eat at a lot of PHO restaurants and yes Huang Lan cost more, but as for the PHO itself, is one of the better ones in all of Fresno.  The broth is clean and flavorful, as for the meat it is fresh including the veggies.
If your looking for cost effective, go where you like, but you do pay for what you get, a pretty darn good bowl of PHO.</review>

<Text>I always have to laugh when people complain about cleanliness at a legitimate pho restaurant. I hail from the SF Bay Area and the most authentic pho joints I've been to are consistently filthy. It just comes with the territory. That being said, Huong Lan is, hands down, the only decent place to grab a generous helping of pho in all of Fresno County. Their portion sizes are massive for the price and I always walk away happy. Their banh mi and boba thai tea also brings me to my happy place. It's a diamond in the rough, as far as I'm concerned.<//Text><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

< Text>
Great ambience with lots of flat screen TVs everywhere and lots of outdoor seating too! Happy Hour until 7pm. Good food and good service. Just note that two thirds of the indoors is designated as bar seating with high top tables, yet only the bar counter itself is first come first serve seating. The high top tables require you to put your name down and wait. The chicken tacos are great. The fried mushrooms are great. The fried pickles are not that great because they're thick sliced and the breading is falling off. The Bourbon Honey Mustard is my favorite wing sauce.</Text>

It was a Thursday evening and I had spent my whole evening playing basketball. My teammates and I were exhausted and we shared a common interest in going to buffalo wild wings. We ubered to the nearest one and saw there would be a wait. We asked and they said it would be a mere 20 minutes. We decided to wait and went outside, however after 20 minutes we were not even close to being shown to a table.

I managed to lift my head  and looked despairingly at my teammates. The bleak look in their eyes told me that we couldn't do this much longer. Our bodies desperately needed calories...

< review>
For the last 2 years every Thursday my wife and I go to Buffalo Wild Wings. We have our go to spots but also try new locations. This particular location is literally 2 blocks from our house, but we try to avoid it when we can. They are over staffed however still manage terrible and slow service. The food is always dry even after we say extra wet, and never consistent. Multiple times our mozzarella sticks have come out cold, the cheese inside is literally a block.

If you do come to this locations ask to sit in Bills section, best server there.

<review>REVIEW FOR THIS LOCATION ONLY:

STAFF AND SERVICE: 1/5
Service is pretty slow, wait staff will almost always conveniently forget to add points to your account after you leave, and they often take more than one attempt to get your order correct for takeaways.

Ricardo, the manager, forgot twice to follow through on his promise to send gift card for takeaway orders they messed up. Convenient again, right?

AMBIENCE AND LOCATION: 3/5
Situated in the heart of Orange County‚Äôs premier shopping area, South Coast Plaza, this location is pretty big with plenty of seating capacity and options. Sports and channel selection is always on spot. Parking can be an issue on weekends and Tue/Thurs nights.

FOOD: 3/5
The wings are amazing, although they are usually out of few sauces on the list, especially the new and limited-time ones. < Review>
i came to this restaurant  during opening week and it was horrible.  1st, there were waiters who randomly went to tables asking if we ordered appetizers, if we ordered more utenzils, they took us another tables drinks, the waiters were very unorganized and did not know what food n drinks went to which table.

we were seated outside and asked them to roll the curtains down because the sun was hittting us in the face...apparently the curtains dont roll down.

when it came to paying...it took our server 20 mins to bring the check.  i walked up to the front and payed there.  i asked to talk to a manager and they couldnt find one...really?

i will gladly now drive past this one to go to another buffalo wild wings.< /Review>

Rolled in last week to check it out. Sat at he bar, ordered a beer (or 3) watched a little football, paid my tab and was out Rolled into the bar tonight (Monday, Jan 5 super slow, holiday BS over) sat at a bar table and after being passed up by 4 or 5 servers was finally greeted by a gal who asked, if this is where I was gonna sit - in other words, how dare you sit a table meant for 4 persons Mr Single guy! Oh shizznat there goes my check average! Yes miss not so interesting server girl, this is where I'm gonna sit can you, please bring me a Dos Equis....What I'm sorry, did you say you need to see my ID? Oh wow, why thank you, thank you for the compliment or should I say insult...I'm 54 years young why in the hell are you asking for my ID? Policy, policy my a**....where's the manager! Along comes mini Mex, all 5 foot nothing and who irreverently addresses me with a greeting of "hey boss what's up? I got your boss right here! After mini Mex tried unsuccessfully to explain their "We ID everyone policy" I unapologetically dropped a couple "F" bombs and opted out of this below average establishment. BWW spent alotta money building this place however after my shameful and embarrassing experience they should restrategize their ID policies and train their managers and servers to interact with guests on a more sophisticated, intelligent level<//Review>
